Zvezda , a rising star...</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#212141><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uherdervazaelle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>HerderVazaelle</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>27</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>2/21/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>10:49:43 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: New monster AI</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Nope, while sugar coating by adding a bunch of useless stuff and some needed stuff, verant has slipped the Biggest game change in of all.  This is a repost from our private guild board that I wrote.<br>
<br>
Ok, lets look at this blow by blow...<br>
<br>
Druid/Shaman Changes:<br>
The reason for these changes is that people were complaining that shamans and druids cant keep up the healing. While true in some respect, Druids and Shamans will never be the healers Clerics are because they aren't dedicated to the job like clerics. Druids snaring, dotting and thorning while shammies are buffing, regrowthing, slowing. If you are going to make Druids and Shaman effective as Clerics, just make them clerics and be done with it. Druids and Shaman, this is just going to make your already tight mana pool that much tighter and if the general playerbase expects you to heal, you are going to hate this &quot;upgrade&quot;. The only change I agree with is reducing wakes recast time to 90 seconds and the reduced fizzle rate. <br>
<br>
Hybrid Changes:<br>
I have never played a hybrid but these changes are pretty nice. Some of the spells are useless such as celestial cleansing at 59 (superior heal is a better spell in all respects and that is gained at 57, why even bother?)<br>
<br>
However, the reason Hybrids are having a tough time hasn't disappeared and these changes seem a band aid to cover the glaring inequalities in the high end game. <br>
<br>
Enchanter Changes:<br>
Enchanters will be nerfed, I can guarantee it. Not sure if it is in this patch or the next patch but the rumor mill is that clarity regen will be lessened while mana regen of all classes increased. Ambivalent on this as clarity isn't the reason I play an enchanter. Once again, the problem enchanters are having isn't addressed.<br>
<br>
Bard Changes:<br>
Bard changes seem positive and I think Verant is looking at the numbers of people who play bards and find it extremely lacking. Bards will be the biggest benefactor of nerfs to enchanters. Bards should soon look to be getting a good portion of the enchanters crowd control abilities in a stronger format. Not only that, bards will have the ability to tank much longer than enchanters. Knowing Verant, they will go overboard on the enchanter nerf and too little on bards, making both classes frustrated at not being able to do crowd control anymore.<br>
<br>
The miscellaneous changes are nice but I can assure you, for every &quot;enchancement&quot; that Verant has given, 3 stealth nerfs are present. Tracking got a much needed boost and for that I suppose one should be happy. The hate list changes scare me due to the way the 50+ game works. <br>
<br>
Quite honestly, Tash does have a big agro. But I would rather have that agro than the cleric. If you don't agree with me now, you soon will.<br>
<br>
Having a rogue may become a liability now and their ability to dish out massive damage is now gone. Rogues will be expiring much faster now unless you have 2 healers in the group. Honestly, if the cleric casts CH on the tank, lives through that, how often do you think a superior heal is going to go to the rogue who is probably going to be either #1 or #2 on the hate list? I see clerics either dying early from healing the rogue or just saying screw it, let the rogue die, I will rez him, the tank is needed more at this point.<br>
<br>
I am not being negative about seemingly positive changes to the game. I am being a realist. This game has been out for quite some time and Verant is desperately trying to get a handle on it. I wish they would focus more on the mobs and content and not worry so much about class envy. Sure some of the changes were needed and for that I applaud them. <br>
<br>
I am eager to see how this works if nothing else than to confirm or deny my guesses.<br>
<br>
